  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.3861" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <dateline>Balt<hi rendition="#sup">o</hi> Mar 9, 1883.</dateline>
        <opener>Dear Sir,</opener>
        <p>According to my word sent you on leaving New Orleans I have today seen <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.5347">Dr. Basil L. Gildersleeve</persName> of the Johns Hopkins Univ’y of this city (Baltimore) editor of the American Journal of Philology<note
            n="1" place="foot"
              type="editorial">
A leading southern U.S. scholar of his time, educated in Germany, <persName
              ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.5347">Gildersleeve</persName> (1831-1924) held the Greek chair at <ref
              type="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.5346">John Hopkins University</ref>, founded the quarterly <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.3344">American Journal of Philology</ref> and remained its editor for 40 years (Briggs 1998).</note> and he has kindly consented to send to you in my name the number of that publication containing the article<note
            n="2" place="foot" type="editorial">See footnote 1 (<ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.letter.3860">Briefnummer 1483</ref>).</note> to which I referred in my letter from New Orleans. It gives me great pleasure to do even so slight a thing for you as to procure this article. The titles of my works in America are “Old Creole Days”, “The Grandissimes”, and “Madame Delphine”<note
            n="3" place="foot" type="editorial">

            <bibl>


Cable (1879)
</bibl>, <bibl>


Cable (1880)
</bibl>, <bibl>


Cable (1881)
</bibl>.</note> but I assure you their rendering of Creole dialect is not of nearly so much value as that given in the magazine which goes to you today <pb
            facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/> Have you Thomas’s grammar of the Creole language, published in Trinidad<note n="4"
            place="foot" type="editorial">
            <bibl>
              <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.bibliography#BIBL.2738">Thomas (1869)</ref>
            </bibl>.</note>? It would be invaluable to your purposes.</p>
        <closer>
          <salute>With great respect, I am yours truly,</salute>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1244">G.W. Cable</persName>
          </signed>
        </closer>
      </div>
    </body>
